{"parentUuid":"e410ce28-f036-422a-9c30-d7be1981f879","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"afa5e38c6946052d0","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01PPdSweaEj2ANV6pSNHa1uH","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01DDQPLeStjdFBUSvbMbL3CD","name":"WebSearch","input":{"query":"A-MEM agentic memory episodic semantic consolidation LLM agent benchmark results"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1003,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5631,"cache_read_input_tokens":6409,"output_tokens":331,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5631},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1003,"output_tokens":331,"cache_read_input_tokens":6409,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5631,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5631,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"tools_changed","cache_missed_input_tokens":8030}}},"requestId":"req_011CcFieeDw9siZQzttLwreW","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"e17bfad0-1ed5-4a2d-a427-6d291857172a","timestamp":"2026-06-21T03:46:35.902Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
{"parentUuid":"e17bfad0-1ed5-4a2d-a427-6d291857172a","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"ea5deda3-2082-4e82-9e86-49535c9f9f1d","agentId":"afa5e38c6946052d0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01DDQPLeStjdFBUSvbMbL3CD","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"A-MEM agentic memory episodic semantic consolidation LLM agent benchmark results\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"A-Mem: Agentic Memory for LLM Agents\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2502.12110\"},{\"title\":\"AMA-Bench: Evaluating Long-Horizon Memory for Agentic Applications\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2602.22769\"},{\"title\":\"A-Mem: Agentic Memory for LLM Agents | OpenReview\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FiM0M8gcct\"},{\"title\":\"Architecture and Orchestration of Memory Systems in AI Agents\",\"url\":\"https://www.analyticsvidhya.com/blog/2026/04/memory-systems-in-ai-agents/\"},{\"title\":\"AI Meets Brain: Memory Systems from Cognitive Neuroscience to Autonomous Agents\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.23343\"},{\"title\":\"ICLR 2026 Workshop Proposal MemAgents: Memory for LLM-Based Agentic Systems\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/pdf?id=U51WxL382H\"},{\"title\":\"Memory for Autonomous LLM Agents: Mechanisms, Evaluation, and Emerging Frontiers\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2603.07670v1\"},{\"title\":\"Amory: Building Coherent Narrative-Driven Agent Memory through Agentic Reasoning\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.06282\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, I found information about A-MEM and related memory systems for LLM agents. Here's what I found:\n\n## A-MEM: Agentic Memory for LLM Agents\n\nA-MEM is a novel agentic memory system for LLM agents that can dynamically organize memories in an agentic way, designed to help agents leverage historical experiences despite limitations in current memory systems.\n\n### Key Features\n\nA-MEM designs a flexible and universal memory system that supports LLM agents' long-term interactions through comprehensive notes, which integrate multiple representations including structured textual attributes and embedding vectors for similarity matching, and analyzes the historical memory repository to establish meaningful connections based on semantic similarities and shared attributes.\n\n### Benchmark Results\n\nA-MEM consistently outperforms all baseline approaches across all metrics.\n\n### Memory Types and Consolidation\n\nThe broader context of LLM agent memory systems includes multi-layered memory models including short-term working memory and long-term episodic, semantic, and procedural memory, with effective memory management techniques such as semantic consolidation, intelligent forgetting, and conflict resolution.\n\nAdditionally, research discusses interactions among memory types including relationships between episodic and semantic memory and between working and long-term memory, and describes conversion pathways such as consolidation from episodic to semantic memory.\n\nFor more detailed benchmark results and technical specifications, you can access the full paper at arxiv.org/pdf/2502.12110.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"775aa290-1c68-4fd3-b9f8-8ade078fe2b4","timestamp":"2026-06-21T03:47:02.691Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"A-MEM agentic memory episodic semantic consolidation LLM agent benchmark results","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01WTcTERQJRXAze8fw9RAxYa","content":[{"title":"A-Mem: Agentic Memory for LLM Agents","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2502.12110"},{"title":"AMA-Bench: Evaluating Long-Horizon Memory for Agentic Applications","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2602.22769"},{"title":"A-Mem: Agentic Memory for LLM Agents | OpenReview","url":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=FiM0M8gcct"},{"title":"Architecture and Orchestration of Memory Systems in AI Agents","url":"https://www.analyticsvidhya.com/blog/2026/04/memory-systems-in-ai-agents/"},{"title":"AI Meets Brain: Memory Systems from Cognitive Neuroscience to Autonomous Agents","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2512.23343"},{"title":"ICLR 2026 Workshop Proposal MemAgents: Memory for LLM-Based Agentic Systems","url":"https://openreview.net/pdf?id=U51WxL382H"},{"title":"Memory for Autonomous LLM Agents: Mechanisms, Evaluation, and Emerging Frontiers","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2603.07670v1"},{"title":"Amory: Building Coherent Narrative-Driven Agent Memory through Agentic Reasoning","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.06282"}]},"Based on the search results, I found information about A-MEM and related memory systems for LLM agents. Here's what I found:\n\n## A-MEM: Agentic Memory for LLM Agents\n\nA-MEM is a novel agentic memory system for LLM agents that can dynamically organize memories in an agentic way, designed to help agents leverage historical experiences despite limitations in current memory systems.\n\n### Key Features\n\nA-MEM designs a flexible and universal memory system that supports LLM agents' long-term interactions through comprehensive notes, which integrate multiple representations including structured textual attributes and embedding vectors for similarity matching, and analyzes the historical memory repository to establish meaningful connections based on semantic similarities and shared attributes.\n\n### Benchmark Results\n\nA-MEM consistently outperforms all baseline approaches across all metrics.\n\n### Memory Types and Consolidation\n\nThe broader context of LLM agent memory systems includes multi-layered memory models including short-term working memory and long-term episodic, semantic, and procedural memory, with effective memory management techniques such as semantic consolidation, intelligent forgetting, and conflict resolution.\n\nAdditionally, research discusses interactions among memory types including relationships between episodic and semantic memory and between working and long-term memory, and describes conversion pathways such as consolidation from episodic to semantic memory.\n\nFor more detailed benchmark results and technical specifications, you can access the full paper at arxiv.org/pdf/2502.12110."],"durationSeconds":8.05784370899992,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e17bfad0-1ed5-4a2d-a427-6d291857172a","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main"}
